    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-03-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-05-09T13:21:49Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p> Recognizes the enduring value of the International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination (ICERD) as a cornerstone of global efforts to combat racial discrimination and uphold human rights.</p> <p>Commends the United States for meeting its ICERD reporting obligations.</p> <p>Calls upon the U.S. government to support existing laws and programs aimed at redressing past injustices that have contributed to ongoing racial discrimination and present day disparities. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
